1. **Address the "Lévy-Lorentz" Specifics in Step 6**: Step 6 currently focuses on Sisyphus cooling and PM maps for the effective Langevin analysis. The Lévy-Lorentz gas is a crucial mechanism for understanding "geometric" Lévy flights. I suggest including the Lévy-Lorentz gas in the drift-diffusion analysis to see if it can be mapped to an effective Langevin equation with state-dependent diffusion, which would provide a powerful contrast to the Sisyphus cooling (which is momentum-dependent).

